might not be destroyed,

00:10:06.389 --> 00:10:09.389
but have everlasting life.

00:10:09.389 --> 00:10:12.389
The world that God loved

00:10:12.389 --> 00:10:17.389
included atheists and enemies of God.

00:10:17.389 --> 00:10:19.389
In line with this,

00:10:19.389 --> 00:10:22.389
Jesus said in Matthew 544-45,

00:10:22.389 --> 00:10:26.389
continue to love your enemies

00:10:26.389 --> 00:10:29.389
and to pray for those who persecute you

00:10:29.389 --> 00:10:32.389
so that you may prove yourselves

00:10:32.389 --> 00:10:36.389
sons of your father who is in the heavens.

00:10:36.389 --> 00:10:40.389
But how are we to love our enemies?

00:10:40.389 --> 00:10:43.389
We don't need to have a faction for them,

00:10:43.389 --> 00:10:47.389
but we need to show principled love,

00:10:47.389 --> 00:10:50.389
agape in Greek,

00:10:50.389 --> 00:10:53.389
Romans 12.20 says,

00:10:53.389 --> 00:10:55.389
if your enemy is hungry,

00:10:55.389 --> 00:10:57.389
feed him,

00:10:57.389 --> 00:11:00.389
give him something to drink.

00:11:00.389 --> 00:11:03.389
If we are to love our enemies,

00:11:03.389 --> 00:11:08.389
are we not to love even much more our brothers?

00:11:08.389 --> 00:11:14.389
Aside from love for relatives in Greek,

00:11:14.389 --> 00:11:16.389
Christians need to display

00:11:16.389 --> 00:11:21.389
four types of love toward the brothers.

00:11:21.389 --> 00:11:25.389
The first type of love is based on principles.

00:11:25.389 --> 00:11:28.389
Greek agape,

00:11:28.389 --> 00:11:32.960
and the verb to it is agapau.

00:11:32.960 --> 00:11:35.960
The noun agape appears more frequently

00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:37.960
than the other terms.

00:11:37.960 --> 00:11:41.960
Agape carries the meaning of love guided by principles,

00:11:41.960 --> 00:11:47.529
true or false.

00:11:47.529 --> 00:11:51.529
Agape does not include affection.

00:11:51.529 --> 00:11:53.529
Actually, the answer is,

00:11:53.529 --> 00:11:56.529
have true and have false.

00:11:56.529 --> 00:12:01.529
Agape may or may not include affection and fondness,

00:12:01.529 --> 00:12:05.529
depending on the circumstances.

00:12:05.529 --> 00:12:10.529
A second type of love is expressed by a verb in Greek,

00:12:10.529 --> 00:12:13.529
and that is filio.

00:12:13.529 --> 00:12:16.529
It refers to having affection,

00:12:16.529 --> 00:12:21.529
being fond of a friend or an object.

00:12:21.529 --> 00:12:25.029
The related noun is filia,

00:12:25.029 --> 00:12:29.029
but this word occurs only once in the Greek scriptures,

00:12:29.029 --> 00:12:34.029
saying that one should not have filia or love for the world.

00:12:34.029 --> 00:12:38.029
James 4 verse 4.

00:12:38.029 --> 00:12:42.029
Let us now consider some examples of affection.

00:12:42.029 --> 00:12:46.029
Jesus felt affection for his friend Lazarus,

00:12:46.029 --> 00:12:49.029
so he gave way to tears

00:12:49.029 --> 00:12:52.029
when standing in front of Lazarus' tomb.

00:12:53.029 --> 00:12:57.029
John 11, 35, 36.

00:12:57.029 --> 00:12:59.029
In Proverbs 831,

00:12:59.029 --> 00:13:01.029
Jesus in his pre-human existence

00:13:01.029 --> 00:13:07.029
said he was especially fond of mankind.

00:13:07.029 --> 00:13:09.029
This relationship existed also

00:13:09.029 --> 00:13:13.029
and still exists between Jehovah and Jesus.

00:13:13.029 --> 00:13:15.029
At John 335,

00:13:15.029 --> 00:13:19.029
we learned that Jehovah feels love agape for his son,

00:13:19.029 --> 00:13:24.029
but his feelings are not limited to that type of love.

00:13:24.029 --> 00:13:31.029
In John 520, Jesus said the Father has affection for the son.

00:13:31.029 --> 00:13:35.029
Certainly, God's agape love for Jesus Christ

00:13:35.029 --> 00:13:38.029
is coupled with much affection.

00:13:38.029 --> 00:13:44.340
Our love for our brother should likewise also extend

00:13:44.340 --> 00:13:47.340
beyond mere agape love.

00:13:47.340 --> 00:13:52.980
We should develop affection for each.

00:13:52.980 --> 00:13:55.980
Twice, Jesus asked Peter if he loved him,

00:13:55.980 --> 00:13:58.980
using the verb agapeau.

00:13:58.980 --> 00:14:01.980
Both times Peter earnestly affirmed

00:14:01.980 --> 00:14:07.980
that he had affection for Jesus using the more intimate word filio,

00:14:07.980 --> 00:14:13.980
according to John 21 verses 15 through 17.

00:14:13.980 --> 00:14:18.980
How could Peter show his affection for Jesus?

00:14:18.980 --> 00:14:22.980
Well, something more than a mere inner feeling was needed.

00:14:22.980 --> 00:14:26.980
Peter could prove his affection by shepherding the sheep.

00:14:26.980 --> 00:14:35.259
Jesus said, initiative is action is proof of affection.

00:14:35.259 --> 00:14:38.259
It's true in John 13, 35, Jesus said,

00:14:38.259 --> 00:14:41.259
by this all will know that you are my disciples

00:14:41.259 --> 00:14:44.259
if you have love among yourselves.

00:14:44.259 --> 00:14:47.259
And here he used the word agape.

00:14:47.259 --> 00:14:51.259
But it is not enough to have agape for our brothers.

00:14:51.259 --> 00:14:53.259
Why?

00:14:53.259 --> 00:14:58.259
Well, it is not so difficult to show agape love for all brothers,

00:14:58.259 --> 00:15:02.259
but it is difficult to have affection for all brothers.

00:15:02.259 --> 00:15:08.259
It might be challenging to show affection.

00:15:08.259 --> 00:15:13.259
One reason is because some have personality traits

00:15:13.259 --> 00:15:16.259
that we find difficult to tolerate.

00:15:16.259 --> 00:15:20.259
Perhaps one has the habit of engaging in negative gossip

00:15:20.259 --> 00:15:23.259
or complaints about many things.

00:15:23.259 --> 00:15:28.259
As imperfect humans, all of us need to work on developing

00:15:28.259 --> 00:15:35.259
not only agape love, but also affection for all of our brothers.

00:15:35.259 --> 00:15:40.259
But even affection is not quite enough.

00:15:40.259 --> 00:15:45.259
With that in mind, what other form of love do we need to display?

00:15:45.259 --> 00:15:50.259
We need to feel tender affection.

00:15:50.259 --> 00:15:54.259
In Romans chapter 12 verse 10,

00:15:54.259 --> 00:16:00.259
the word philostargos is used, and it means more than affection.

00:16:00.259 --> 00:16:03.259
In Greek, it means tender affection.

00:16:03.259 --> 00:16:09.259
According to the inside book, volume 1 page 55.

00:16:09.259 --> 00:16:12.259
And the Apostle Paul encouraged Christians

00:16:12.259 --> 00:16:17.259
